  <description><![CDATA[<p>Located in the heart of the village and surrounded by mountains and snow, the Sunstar is a spacious hotel offering an excellent range of facilities in a convenient location for the skiing and resort amenities. </p>
<h2>Relaxation facilities </h2>
<p>Recharge your batteries and relax in the Sunstars spa area, all with unbeatable views of the Eiger. The hotels Wellness Oasis area is the best place to pit stop before dinner, with access to a large swimming pool, log cabin sauna, roman thermal baths with 4 climate zones and experience showers. Discover the massage and beauty therapies available and really give your muscles some tender loving care.</p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>Breakfast is served in the Ambiance restaurant and you'll have a range of foods to get you ready for the energetic day ahead - fuel up with a variety of breads, muesli, fruits, egg dishes, regional meats and cheeses and a range of exquisite teas. For dinner you can expect a varied buffet using fresh and sustainable products. There is also a Swiss speciality restaurant, the Adlerstube which serves delicious fondues and their speciality tomahawk steaks. </p>
<p>If you'd like to end the evening with a casual and cosy atmosphere, we'd recommend visiting the hotels bar and lounge area, where you'll be able to sit back and relax, order a drink and enjoy the views of the impressive Eiger Mountain.</p>
<h2>Location </h2>
<p>Hotel Sunstar is located at the base of the Eiger North Face peaks and offers some incredible views. And whilst you appreciate the scenery, you'll also be able to explore the mountains as the 'First' gondola is directly opposite the hotel meaning you'll have quick and easy access to <a data-udi="umb://document/1a5883a1530346a9ab78607d76c2e656" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1a5883a1530346a9ab78607d76c2e656}" title="Jungfrau Ski Region">Jungfrau ski area</a>. </p>
<p>No matter what room you stay in, you're guaranteed great views. North facing views have views of the Wetterhorn and first Mountains and South facing rooms have views of the Eiger and Kleine Scheidegg mountains.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
